The BBC chat show host celebrated his nuptials in his native west Cork on Saturday with more than 100 guests. It is understood the 59-year-old multple Bafta award winner held a lavish reception at the 18th century Bantry House estate. The identity of Graham's husband remains a mystery with the celebrity opting to keep his relationship out of the spotlight. A second day of festivities was held at his home by the harbour, near the tiny village of Ahakista. Singer Lulu, 73, is understood to have performed at the stylish bash.